        <div class="snippet-answer">
          <p><strong>Direct marketing</strong> is a strategy that communicates directly with targeted customers without intermediaries. Instead of running ads on mass media and hoping the right person sees them, you reach a defined audience through email, SMS, direct mail, or targeted paid ads and ask for a <strong>specific measurable response</strong> &mdash; a click, a reply, a purchase.</p>
        </div>

        <div class="term-meta-strip">
          <div class="tms-cell">
            <div class="tms-label">Primary metric</div>
            <div class="tms-value">Response rate</div>
          </div>
          <div class="tms-cell">
            <div class="tms-label">Category</div>
            <div class="tms-value">General Marketing</div>
          </div>
          <div class="tms-cell">
            <div class="tms-label">Common channels</div>
            <div class="tms-value">Email &middot; SMS &middot; Mail &middot; Paid ads</div>
          </div>
          <div class="tms-cell">
            <div class="tms-label">Difficulty</div>
            <div class="tms-value">Beginner</div>
          </div>
        </div>

        <p class="lede-p">Direct marketing is the oldest measurable marketing discipline &mdash; and still the highest-ROI channel for most businesses. Instead of buying attention on someone else's audience, you build your own list and sell to it directly.</p>

        <h2 id="what-is">What is direct marketing?</h2>
        <p>Direct marketing is any promotional message sent from your brand to a specific audience with the aim of prompting an immediate response. It skips retailers, publishers, and media intermediaries and delivers the message straight to the buyer. The measurement standard is not impressions or reach but <strong>response rate</strong> &mdash; how many recipients took the requested action.</p>
        <p>The core channels are:</p>
        <ul>
          <li><strong>Email marketing</strong> &mdash; the highest-ROI direct channel</li>
          <li><strong>SMS / WhatsApp</strong> &mdash; near-real-time direct messaging</li>
          <li><strong>Direct mail</strong> &mdash; postcards, letters, catalogues</li>
          <li><strong>Telemarketing</strong> &mdash; outbound sales calls</li>
          <li><strong>Targeted paid ads</strong> &mdash; ads with a specific response CTA (e.g. "buy now")</li>
        </ul>

        <div class="callout callout-info">
          <div class="callout-label">Direct marketing vs branding</div>
          <p>Direct marketing asks for a response <em>now</em> and gets measured on conversion. Brand marketing invests in mental availability over months. Both matter &mdash; but a direct-response campaign that can't be measured is doing neither job.</p>
        </div>

        <h2 id="why-it-matters">Why direct marketing matters</h2>
        <ol>
          <li><strong>Owned audience.</strong> Email and SMS lists are your asset &mdash; they don't disappear when an algorithm changes.</li>
          <li><strong>Every response is attributable.</strong> Unlike broadcast advertising, direct marketing lets you tie revenue to a specific send.</li>
          <li><strong>Cheaper per conversion.</strong> Talking to warm audiences almost always beats acquiring cold ones.</li>
          <li><strong>Compounding returns.</strong> A well-nurtured list keeps producing revenue with minimal incremental cost.</li>
          <li><strong>Better resource allocation.</strong> Measurable response data drives smarter budget decisions across the funnel.</li>
        </ol>

        <h2 id="how-it-works">How direct marketing works</h2>
        <p>The workflow is unusually simple and unusually strict.</p>

        <div class="url-flow">
          <span class="uf-comment"># The direct-response loop</span><br>
          1. <span class="uf-label">Segment</span> your list by behaviour or lifecycle stage<br>
          2. <span class="uf-label">Write</span> a message with one clear call to action<br>
          3. <span class="uf-label">Send</span> at the right time to the right segment<br>
          4. <span class="uf-label">Measure</span> response rate, conversion, and revenue<br>
          5. <span class="uf-label">Iterate</span> subject lines, offers, and segments<br>
          <br>
          <span class="uf-comment"># The channel is a delivery mechanism. The list, offer, and copy do the work.</span>
        </div>

        <h2 id="types">Types of direct marketing</h2>
        <div class="table-wrap">
          <table>
            <thead>
              <tr><th>Channel</th><th>Response window</th><th>Cost profile</th><th>Best for</th></tr>
            </thead>
            <tbody>
              <tr class="row-highlight"><td><strong>Email marketing</strong></td><td>Hours</td><td>Low fixed cost</td><td>Highest ROI &mdash; nearly every business</td></tr>
              <tr><td><strong>SMS / WhatsApp</strong></td><td>Minutes</td><td>Per-message fees</td><td>Time-sensitive offers, appointment reminders</td></tr>
              <tr><td><strong>Direct mail</strong></td><td>2-6 weeks</td><td>High per-piece cost</td><td>High-value B2B and premium consumer</td></tr>
              <tr><td><strong>Telemarketing</strong></td><td>Immediate</td><td>Labour-intensive</td><td>B2B outbound sales</td></tr>
              <tr><td><strong>Direct-response ads</strong></td><td>Days</td><td>Auction-based</td><td>Scaling with a proven offer</td></tr>
            </tbody>
          </table>
        </div>

        <h2 id="examples">Real direct marketing examples</h2>
        <p>Two anonymised examples from theStacc's audit archive:</p>

        <h3>1. Local fitness studio &middot; Facebook direct-response ads</h3>
        <div class="url-flow">
          <span class="uf-comment"># 3-month optimisation</span><br>
          Cost per lead: <span class="uf-old">$41</span> <span class="uf-arrow">&rarr;</span> <span class="uf-new">$24.60</span><br>
          Reduction: <span class="uf-new">40% lower CPL</span><br>
